le, managing all document content and state.\\n\\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx, line 331): The Calc (spreadsheet) document class that encapsulates all spreadsheet data, formulas, and formatting. This is the central data structure for the Calc module.\\n\\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx, line 338): The Impress/Draw document class that extends FmFormModel and manages presentation and drawing content, including slides, pages, and graphical elements.\\n\\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx, line 103): The LibreOffice application framework entry point, implemented as a singleton that inherits from SfxShell. It manages global application state, window management, filters, and macro/scripting functionality.\\n\\nThese classes form the hierarchical architecture where SfxObjectShell is the common base, and each module (Writer, Calc, Impress/Draw) provides specialized implementations. SfxApplication provides the application-level framework that coordinates all these document instances.\"\n}\n",
